Package back.calculator.types

Class MyNumber

java.lang.Object
back.calculator.types.MyNumber
All Implemented Interfaces:
Expression
Direct Known Subclasses:
NotANumber
public class MyNumber extends Object implements Expression
MyNumber is a concrete class that represents arithmetic numbers, which are a special kind of Expressions, just like operations are.

A number is represented by a real part and an imaginary part which are both AbstractValue. If the imaginary part is zero, the number is considered real.

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Convert a number into a String to allow it to be printed.

      The number will be printed according to its representation.
      Cartesian: a + bi
      Polar: r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))
      Exponential: r exp(theta i)
